---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import NewsletterFooter from '../../components/NewsletterFooter.astro';

const entries = await getCollection('ls');
const entryMap = Object.fromEntries(entries.map(e => [e.id, e]));

const GRID_ORDER = [
  'helping-heuristics',
  'nine-whys',
  'appreciative-interviews',
  'ecocycle-planning',
  'celebrity-interview',
  '25-10-crowdsourcing',
  'open-space-technology',
  'wise-crowds',
  'tiny-monsters',
  'wicked-questions',
  'heard-seen-respected',
  'narrative-reauthoring',
  '15percent-solutions',
  'triz',
  'min-specs',
  'user-experience-fishbowl',
  'spiral-journal',
  'conversation-cafe',
  'troika-consulting',
  'impromptu-networking',
  '1-2-4-all',
  'mad-tea-party',
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Field notes from my Liberating Structures practice"
  description="Liberating Structures field notes by Tomomi Sasaki."
  canonicalUrl="https://www.ripplet.org/liberating-structures"
>
  <Header currentPath="/liberating-structures" />
  <main>
    <div class="page-content">
      <h1 class="entry-title">Liberating Structures field notes</h1>

      <div class="intro-section">
        {
        <figure class="intro-figure">
          <img src="/liberating-structures/images/image-asset.jpeg" alt="Post workshop mood" />
          <figcaption>Post workshop mood</figcaption>
        </figure>
        }

        <p><a href="https://www.liberatingstructures.com">Liberating Structures</a> are a set of scalable facilitation patterns that orchestrate inclusive, real-time group interactions. </p>

      <p><strong>Field notes</strong> are stories, insights and musings from my facilitation practice as a:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Design consultant facilitating multi-stakeholder workshops for complex enterprise challenges</li>
        <li>Workshop facilitator for design and research communities of practice</li>
        <li>Convener of internal gatherings at my design consultancy</li>
        <li>Teacher and participant in workshop-style training on various topics</li>
      </ul>

      <p>I wrote them per-Structure, between 2019-2020, as a contribution to the LS community's body of knowledge, with a shout out of appreciation to my hosts and cohort at <a href="https://www.greaterthan.works/academy/liberating-structures-studio">Liberating Structures Studio</a> and LS Playground, our alumni practice group.</p>

      </div>


      <div class="featured-grid">
        {GRID_ORDER.map(id => {
          const entry = entryMap[id];
          const href = entry ? `/liberating-structures/${id}` : '#';
          const title = entry?.data.title ?? id;
          const image = entry?.data.image;
          return (
            <a href={href}>
              {image && <img src={`/liberating-structures/images/${image}`} alt={title} />}
              <span>{title}</span>
            </a>
          );
        })}
      </div>

      <h3>Drawing some boundaries…</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>Much of the commercial application of my facilitation practice dwells in the subtle nuances of orchestrating momentum among all kinds of power dynamics in the client organization. A lot of these notes will be about how to navigate unknowable environments as a hired gun, and increasing alignment and confidence towards a broader project goal.</li>
        <li>I am <em>not</em> of the school that believes facilitation to be a neutral act. As a designer, whatever intent I hold for the challenge at stake will be tightly woven in how I host and facilitate conversations.</li>
        <li>It's rare that I host workshops that are a pure string of LS. I draw on other schools of facilitation to design for activities like synthesis, modeling, decision making, assessing risks, mapping scenarios, project planning, etc.</li>
        <li>This is not: an introduction to Liberating Structures, comprehensive instructions on how to run them, or particularly actionable for non-facilitation practitioners. </li>
      </ul>

      <p>If you aren't familiar with Liberating Structures yet, you're in for a treat. Visit the official <a href="https://www.liberatingstructures.com">website</a> and join the Slack group. <a href="https://medium.com/the-liberators">The Liberators</a> publication is also an amazing place to learn the nitty gritty. To jump in with facilitation, start accumulating lived experiences as a participant.</p>

      <NewsletterFooter maxWidth="960px" />
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 60px 30px 80px;
  }


  p { margin: 0 0 20px; }


  a { color: inherit; text-decoration: underline; }
  a:hover { opacity: 0.6; }

  .intro-figure {
    float: right;
    margin: 0 0 16px 24px;
    width: 260px;
  }

  .intro-figure img { width: 100%; display: block; }

  .intro-figure figcaption {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #999;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .intro-section::after {
    content: '';
    display: table;
    clear: both;
  }

  .featured-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(140px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .featured-grid a {
    display: block;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: #222;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .featured-grid a:hover {
    color: #0085bd;
    border-color: #aaa;
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .featured-grid a:hover img { opacity: 0.85; }

  .featured-grid img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    object-fit: contain;
    padding: 10px 18% 4px;
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .featured-grid span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 8px 10px;
    line-height: 1.4em;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-content { padding: 40px 20px 60px; }

    .intro-figure {
      float: none;
      width: 100%;
      margin: 0 0 24px 0;
    }

    .featured-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(120px, 1fr));
      gap: 10px;
    }
  }
</style>
